  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>This is a sample post showing the authoring workflow for the blog. You can edit this file in VS Code with the Quarto extension and use the visual editor when that is helpful.</p>
<p>Inline math works with dollar delimiters, as in <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?X_1,%20%5Cldots,%20X_n%20%5Csim%20P">. Display math works with double-dollar delimiters:</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cbar%20X_n%20=%20%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bn%7D%5Csum_%7Bi=1%7D%5En%20X_i.%0A"></p>
<p>For example, if <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?X_i"> are independent with mean <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cmu">, then</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cmathbb%7BE%7D%5B%5Cbar%20X_n%5D%20=%20%5Cmu.%0A"></p>
