</div>
<div class="callout-body-container callout-body">
<p>This site uses MathJax, which is a good default for research math because it supports a broad subset of LaTeX notation.</p>
</div>
</div>
<section id="theorem-style-writing" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="theorem-style-writing">Theorem-style writing</h2>
<p>You can write theorem-like blocks directly in Markdown:</p>
<p><strong>Lemma.</strong> Let <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?X"> be integrable. Then for any constant <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?a">,</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cmathbb%7BE%7D%5BX%20-%20a%5D%20=%20%5Cmathbb%7BE%7D%5BX%5D%20-%20a.%0A"></p>
<p><strong>Proof.</strong> This follows by linearity of expectation. <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Csquare"></p>
<p>Citations also work through Pandoc and Quarto; for example, see <span class="citation" data-cites="robbins1970statistical">(Robbins 1970)</span>.</p>
</section>
